 Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State flanked by his wife, Tamunominini (right), and Aare Musulumi of Yoruband, Edo and Delta, Alhaji Dawud Akinola, during a farewell visit to intending Muslim pilgrims from Oyo for the 2019 hajj in Ibadan…yesterday.  Chairman, Oyo State Pilgrims’ Welfare Board (Muslim Wing), Prof. Ayantunde Malik, who promised that the pilgrims would be well taken care of in Saudi Arabia Kingdom, however, appreciated the Passport Controller Officer, Alhaji Abdulkadir Sule Garo, for his efforts in ensuring that all the intending pilgrims received their international passports before July 15.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .